{
  "text": "(1) First, during high power laser irradiation, a very intense plasma plume is created at the graphite-water interface and pressure and temperature reach their peak values of 1-10 GPa and 5000-6000 K, respectively [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . These values fall in the liquid region of the carbon phase diagram describing the appearance of a melt layer between the plume and graphite of the bulk target.",
